rangeIncludes.comment: An attribute of a geographical object.

domainIncludes.comment: A planar surface specified as one completely round flat shape in the mathematical sense.

The combination of the latitude and longitude forming a graticule, used for specifying the position of any location on the surface of the Earth, without consideration of altitude or depth (reference ISO 19136).
A connection between two points on the surface of the Earth (reference ISO 19136).
A collection of curves on the surface of the Earth (reference ISO 19136).
A collection of points, on the surface of the Earth (reference ISO 19136).
A collection of surfaces on the Earth (reference ISO 19136).
A point on the surface of the Earth (reference ISO 19136).
A figure on the Earth having only two dimensions (reference ISO 19136).
A specified array of points which define a closed loop which is not self intersecting.
A planar surface, defined by one exterior boundary and zero or more interior boundaries. Each interior boundary defines a hole in the polygon.
